'''日本交通'''以[[公路|公路]]、[[铁路|铁路]]、[[航空|航空]]和[[船運|水路]]为主<ref>{{cite web | url=http://loonybg.hubpages.com/hub/Facts-of-Japan-Transportation | title=Facts of Japan - Transportation | accessdate=2013-12-10 | archive-date=2015-09-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906101032/http://loonybg.hubpages.com/hub/Facts-of-Japan-Transportation | dead-url=no }}</ref>，首都[[东京|东京]]是[[日本|日本]]的公路、铁路、水路及航空总枢纽，以及重要的航空[[轉口港|轉口港]]和[[港口|港口]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www1.geo.ntnu.edu.tw/~shensm/Course/CourseWork/AsiaPacific_Stu/Japan/行政.html | title=日本行政區 | accessdate=2013-12-10 | archive-date=2010-03-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100310150656/http://www1.geo.ntnu.edu.tw/~shensm/Course/CourseWork/AsiaPacific_Stu/Japan/%E8%A1%8C%E6%94%BF.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。日本的[[高速公路|高速公路]]收費和徵稅都較其他國家高，但同時亦在公路維修和保養方面投放不少資源<ref>{{cite web | url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9500E3DC1031F932A35750C0A961958260 | title=Japan's Road to Deep Deficit Is Paved With Public Works | publisher=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]] | date=1997 | accessdate=2013-12-13 | archive-date=2009-02-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090204191732/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9500E3DC1031F932A35750C0A961958260 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[節能|節能]]方面也屬世界領先<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.stanford.edu/~plipscy/JapanDPJEnergyEfficiency.pdf | title=A Casualty of Political Transformation? The Politics of Japanese Energy Efficiency in the Transportation Sector, ''Journal of East Asian Studies'' 12:3 | date=2012 | accessdate=2013-12-13 | author=Phillip Y. Lipscy | archive-date=2013-11-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105022353/http://www.stanford.edu/~plipscy/JapanDPJEnergyEfficiency.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

由於日本是個[[島嶼國家|島嶼國家]]，岛與岛之间有[[渡輪|渡輪]]連接，城市之间也有高速公路和[[新干线|新干线]]相连，市内[[自行车|自行车]]、[[摩托车|摩托车]]、[[汽车|汽车]]等各种交通工具均被大规模应用<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.kantsuu.com/riben/101546.shtml | title=图片说明日本交通特色 | accessdate=2013-12-13 | archive-date=2013-12-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213101143/http://www.kantsuu.com/riben/101546.shtml | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

日本的車輛[[道路通行方向#日本|靠左行駛]]<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.neworldjp.com/Show/14226/| title=为什么日本的车流靠左行驶，人流也要靠左站立| accessdate=2013-12-13| archive-date=2013-12-16| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131216181906/http://www.neworldjp.com/Show/14226/| dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

== 鐵路 ==
[[File:Tōkaidō_Shinkansen_700_&_300_001.JPG|thumb]]上的[[新幹線300系電聯車|300系列車]]和[[新幹線700系電聯車|700系列車]]]]
{{main|日本鐵路運輸}}
日本在2010年的铁路运量達226.7億人次，為全球第一<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mlit.go.jp/k-toukei/10/annual/n2-2suii.xls | title=旅客数量月別推移 | accessdate=2013-12-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427024944/http://www.mlit.go.jp/k-toukei/10/annual/n2-2suii.xls | archive-date=2014-04-27 | dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="UIC">{{cite web| url=http://www.uic.asso.fr/railisa| title=UIC database| accessdate=2013-01-23| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050109171536/http://www2.uic.asso.fr/railisa/| archivedate=2005-01-09}}</ref>。[[东京地铁|东京地铁]]亦是世界上流量最大的地铁系统<ref>{{cite web | url=http://geography.about.com/od/urbaneconomicgeography/a/Busiest-Subways.htm | title=Busiest Subways- The World's Busiest Subway Systems | accessdate=2013-12-10 | archive-date=2018-12-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226085249/http://geography.about.com/od/urbaneconomicgeography/a/Busiest-Subways.htm%20 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。日本的铁路密度高，且基本实现电气化，1964年開通的[[新干线|新干线]]就成為了世界首個高速鐵路<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kurogane-rail.jp/osakarm/cosakarm_13.html |title=0系新幹線電車 |accessdate=2013-12-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130829090612/http://www.kurogane-rail.jp/osakarm/cosakarm_13.html |archivedate=2013-08-29 }}</ref>。

日本的鐵路以準時和安全聞名<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.welcome2japan.tw/arrange/transportation/railways.html | title=日本政府觀光局 <nowiki>| 旅遊攻略 | 交通資訊 | 鐵路 </nowiki> | accessdate=2013-12-13 | archive-date=2020-05-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526055206/https://www.welcome2japan.tw/arrange/transportation/railways.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，2006年的[[東海道新幹線|東海道新幹線]]全年的班次平均僅有0.3分鐘延遲<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.jr-central.co.jp/company/ir/annual-report/_pdf/report-2007.pdf|title=Central Japan Railway Company Annual Report 2007|page=14|accessdate=2008-06-24|format=PDF}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> 。如果鐵路班次延遲超過五分鐘，車站站長會在站內透過廣播向乘客道歉，並在每个站的出站处大量發放{{link-ja|延遲證明書|遅延証明書}}，讓受影響人士可以向公司或學校解释迟到原因<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.517japan.com/viewnews-10524.html | title=日本交通体验 人性化的“误点证明书” | date=2010-11-19 | accessdate=2013-12-13 | archive-date=2020-05-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526055253/https://www.517japan.com/viewnews-10524.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。如果班次延遲超過1小時，事件更有可能被登上報紙<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitachi-rail.com/rail_now/column/just_in_time/index.html |title=Corporate Culture as Strong Driving Force for Punctuality- Another "Just in Time" |accessdate=2009-04-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513230217/http://www.hitachi-rail.com/rail_now/column/just_in_time/index.html |archivedate=2008-05-13 }}</ref>。

目前連接[[本州|本州]]和[[北海道|北海道]]，供[[日本國有鐵道|JR]]使用的[[青函隧道|青函隧道]]是世界上第二長的隧道，全長53.85[[公里|公里]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bdcb.cn/shtml/bdcb/20130728/51285.shtml|title=日本青函隧道近54公里 目前世界最长|accessdate=2013-12-15|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215071929/http://bdcb.cn/shtml/bdcb/20130728/51285.shtml|archivedate=2013-12-15}}</ref>。
